title: Google\Cloud\BigQuery\Reservation\V1\CapacityCommitment
name: CapacityCommitment
description:
Capacity commitment is a way to purchase compute capacity for BigQuery jobs (in the form of slots) with some committed period of usage. Annual commitments renew by default. Commitments can be removed after their commitment end time passes.

In order to remove annual commitment, its plan needs to be changed to monthly or flex first. A capacity commitment resource exists as a child resource of the admin project.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.bigquery.reservation.v1.CapacityCommitment

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Output only. The resource name of the capacity commitment, e.g., projects/myproject/locations/US/capacityCommitments/123

params.name: data.commitment_end_time
params.description: Output only. The end of the current commitment period. It is applicable only for ACTIVE capacity commitments.

params.name: data.failure_status
params.description: Output only. For FAILED commitment plan, provides the reason of failure.

params.name: data.renewal_plan
params.description: The plan this capacity commitment is converted to after commitment_end_time passes. Once the plan is changed, committed period is extended according to commitment plan. Only applicable for ANNUAL and TRIAL commitments.
